-- CNN Says U.S. Head Klein Leaving; Jautz to Run Network
-- B y   H e a t h e r   B u r k e
-- 2010-09-24T14:22:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/cnn-president-klein-leaving-as-cable-network-loses-viewers-to-fox-msnbc.html
(Corrects spelling of Jautz in headline)  CNN said Jon Klein, head of
CNN/U.S., is leaving the channel. Ken Jautz is moving from HLN
to CNN/U.S. to run the network as its executive vice president.  Scot Safon assumes the executive vice president role at HLN
and will run the network. The information was contained in a
memo sent to CNN employees.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Heather Burke at 
 hburke2@bloomberg.net  